tPoints

Class TVector3

  • java.lang.Object
    • tPoints.TVector3
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<TVector3>

    public class TVector3
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<TVector3>
    A 3 dimensional vector.
    Used for things that use 3 dimensional vectors.

    It's like a TVector2 except with 50% more axis and like 90% less features.

    Author:
    Tallon Hodge
    See Also:
    TVector2

    • Field Detail

      • lockedAxes

        public TVector3.lockModes lockedAxes
        Forces 2 or 3 axes to be the same.

        WARNING: Will not alter current axis values upon being changed.
        eg: If x = 1 and y == 2, setting lockedAxes to XY will not change the values of x and y
